    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @Kikobeats,\r\n\r\nThat's because the label is directly the string \"25 <= price <=282\" and for the `Range`, there's no child to display contrary to the `Refinement List`.\r\n\r\nIf this structure is not what you want, you can use the [`connectCurrentRefinements`](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/react/connectors/connectCurrentRefinements.html) connector to define your own. By using the connector, you will have access to the prop `items` that have a structure like: \r\n\r\n```json\r\n[{\r\n    \"attributeName\": \"category\",\r\n    \"label\": \"category: \",\r\n    \"currentRefinement\": [\"Sails\"],\r\n    \"items\": [{\r\n        \"label\": \"Sails\"\r\n    }]\r\n}, {\r\n    \"label\": \"4.99 <= price <= 699\",\r\n    \"currentRefinement\": {\r\n        \"min\": 4.99,\r\n        \"max\": 699\r\n    },\r\n    \"attributeName\": \"price\"\r\n}]\r\n```",
